==English==

===Noun===
# Darkness in an area of light, particularly sunlight.
#: ''The old oak tree gave shade in the heat of the day.''
# Something blocking light, particularly in a window.
#: ''Close the shade, please, it's too bright in here.''
# A particular variety of a color.
#: ''I've painted my room in lovely shades of pink and chartreuse.''
# (''slang, always plural'') Sunglasses.
#: ''That model looks way cool in those shades.''
# (''archaic'') A ghost.
#: ''Too long have I been haunted by that shade.''

===Transitive verb===
# To shield from light.
#: ''The old oak tree shaded the lawn in the heat of the day.''
# To alter slightly.
#: ''You'll need to shade your shot slightly to the left.''
#: ''Most politicians will shade the truth if it helps them.''

